cadSoftwareMeasMib.name: cadSoftwareMeasMib

revisions.description: Add global scaling counts and cadCamScaleTable.
Added implementation per utilization interval for cadUpChannelAvgContSlots, cadUpChannelAvgUtil.
Added UGS count / measurements for Time Warner.
Added support for intelligent channel optimization.

cadSWUChannelMeasTable.name: cadSWUChannelMeasTable
cadSWUChannelMeasTable.description: This table contains software counts in the upstream channels.

cadSWUChannelMeasEntry.name: cadSWUChannelMeasEntry
cadSWUChannelMeasEntry.description: List of counts or measurements for a single upstream channel. For Docsis 2.0 CMTSs, an entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstreamChannel (205). For Docsis 1.x CM/CMTSs and Docsis 2.0 CMs, an entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstreamInterface (129).

cadUpChannelIngressCancellationBandwidth.name: cadUpChannelIngressCancellationBandwidth
cadUpChannelIngressCancellationBandwidth.description: The utilization index is a percentage expressing the ratio between minislots reserved for ingress cancellation analysis versus the total number of minislots for upstream transmission. Formula: ingress cancellation bandwidth = (cancellation_minislots_per_second / total_minislots_per_second) * 100%

cadUpChannelMaxUGSLastOneHour.name: cadUpChannelMaxUGSLastOneHour
cadUpChannelMaxUGSLastOneHour.description: This object indicates the maximum number of Unsolicited Grant Service (UGS) allocated on a given upstream in the last one hour. This would be used for the user to evaluate traffic load at any given time of the day.

cadUpChannelAvgUGSLastOneHour.name: cadUpChannelAvgUGSLastOneHour

cadCamScaleUsRangeCount.name: cadCamScaleUsRangeCount
cadCamScaleUsRangeCount.description: Total US channels requiring ranging. Each CM with N channels in-service to this UCAM adds N to the count (e.g., a 4 US bonded CM adds 4 to this count). Unbonded modems add one to the count. For DCAMs, this count is always zero.
